lly inactive. The Company accepts no liability for any injury, illness, or health consequences arising from the use of the App or participation in activities promoted within it.\nStep and calorie data provided by the App are estimates only and may vary significantly from actual values.\n8. Privacy and Data\n\n8.1 Privacy Policy\nYour use of the App is also governed by our Privacy Policy, which is incorporated into these Terms by reference. By using the App, you consent to the collection, use, and processing of your personal data as described in the Privacy Policy.\n\n8.2 Data We Collect\nWe collect personal data you provide during registration (name, date of birth, gender, phone number, profile photo), fitness data obtained through health integrations (steps, calories, distance), usage data (leaderboard position, Season Pass progress, donations), and device and technical data (device type, operating system, app version).\n\n8.3 Third-Party Integrations\nThe App integrates with Apple Health, Google Fit, and Samsung Health. By connecting these services, you authorise the transfer of relevant health data to the App. Your use of these third-party services is subject to their own terms of service and privacy policies.\n\n8.4 Push Notifications\nWith your permission, we may send you push notifications and WhatsApp messages relating to your activity, community goals, mascot updates, and promotions. You may withdraw this permission at any time through your device settings.\n\n8.5 Data Retention\nWe retain your personal data for as long as your account is active or as required to provide our services. Upon account deletion, we will delete your personal data in accordance with applicable law, except where retention is required for legal or regulatory purposes.\n9. Intellectual Property\nAll intellectual property rights in and to the App, including but not limited to software, design, logos, mascot characters, graphics, text, and Content, are owned by or licensed to SIA Dosty. Nothing in these Terms grants you any right, title, or interest in such intellectual property.\nYou are granted a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable licence to install and use the App on your personal device solely for your personal, non-commercial use in accordance with these Terms. This licence terminates immediately upon termination of your account or these Terms.\n10. Third-Party Links and Services\nThe App may contain links to third-party websites or services, including Partner Offers. These links are provided for your convenience only. The Company has no control over and assumes no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party websites or services. Your interactions with third parties are solely between you and the relevant third party.\n11. Disclaimer of Warranties\nTO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. THE COMPANY EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, WHETHER EXPRESS, IMPLIED, STATUTORY, OR OTHERWISE, INCLUDING ANY IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.\nWe do not warrant that: (a) the App will be available uninterrupted or error-free; (b) step data or fitness metrics will be accurate; (c) Partner Offers will be available or valid; or (d) community donation goals will be achieved.\n12. Limitation of Liability\nTO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE COMPANY AND ITS DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, AGENTS, AND LICENSORS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH YOUR USE OF OR INABILITY TO USE THE APP.\nIn no event shall the Company's total aggregate liability to you for all claims arising under or related to these Terms or the App exceed the total amount paid by you to the Company in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to such liability, or AZN 10 (ten Azerbaijani manats) if no such payments have been made.\nSome jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion of certain warranties or limitation of liability for consequential damages; in such jurisdictions, liability is limited to the fullest extent permitted by law.\n13. Indemnification\nYou agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Company and its affiliates, officers, directors, employees, and agents from and against any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, costs, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising out of or relating to: (a) your use of the App; (b) your violation of these Terms; (c) your violation of any applicable law or the rights of any third party; or (d) any fraudulent manipulation of step data.\n14. Term and Termination\n\n14.1 Term\nThese Terms remain in effect for as long as you use the App or maintain an account.\n\n14.2 Termination by You\nYou may delete your account at any time through the App's settings. Deletion of your account constitutes termination of these Terms. Any earned Coins, Season Pass progress, and leaderboard data will be permanently deleted and cannot be recovered.\n\n14.3 Termination by Us\nWe reserve the right to block, suspend, or permanently delete your account and access to the App at any time, with or without prior notice, at our sole discretion, including but not limited to where we reasonably believe that: (a) you have violated any provision of these Terms or our in-App policies; (b) your conduct negatively affects other users, the integrity of the App, or the reputation of the Company; (c) you have engaged in fraudulent, abusive, or manipulative activity; (d) your actions interfere with the operation, security, or fairness of any App feature; or (e) such action is required by law or a competent authority. Blocked or deleted accounts will lose all associated data, including Coins, Season Pass progress, and leaderboard standing, with no entitlement to compensation or refund except where required by applicable law.\n\n14.4 Effect of Termination\nUpon termination, the licence granted to you under these Terms will immediately cease. Clauses that by their nature should survive termination (including Sections 9, 11, 12, 13, 15, and 16) will remain in force.\n15. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution\nThese Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Republic of Latvia, without regard to its conflict of law principles.\nAny dispute arising out of or in connection with these Terms or the App shall first be attempted to be resolved through good-faith negotiation. If not resolved within 30 days, the dispute shall be submitted to the exclusive jurisdiction of the competent courts of Latvia.\nNotwithstanding the above, the Company acknowledges that users in Azerbaijan may have rights under local consumer protection laws that cannot be excluded by agreement. Nothing in these Terms limits any such statutory rights.\n16. Changes to These Terms\nWe reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. If we make material changes, we will notify you via the App, push notification, or email at least 14 days before the changes take effect. Continued use of the App after the effective date of any changes constitutes your acceptance of the revised Terms. If you do not agree to the revised Terms, you must stop using the App.\n17. General Provisions\n\n17.1 Entire Agreement\nThese Terms, together with our Privacy Policy, constitute the entire agreement between you and the Company regarding the App and supersede all prior agreements, representations, and understandings.\n\n17.2 Severability\nIf any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable or invalid, that provision shall be modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable, and the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.\n\n17.3 Waiver\nThe failure of the Company to enforce any provision of